COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 836, L.D. 1261
1 Sec. 3. Community navigators to connect and refer screened-out families
2 to community services. Resolved: That a community navigator under the pilot
3 program shall connect and refer screened-out families to community services. A screened-
4 out family is a family for which there was a report to the department for suspected child
5 abuse or neglect but the department determined that the report of suspected child abuse or
6 neglect did not meet the department's criteria to open a child protective services
7 investigation. Community navigators shall connect and refer to community services
8 screened-out families that would likely benefit from community services for support to
9 prevent the need for intervention by child protective services in the future. Those
10 community services may include, but are not limited to, physical and mental health care,
11 housing assistance, food access assistance, fuel assistance, child care, transportation,
12 employment training and substance use disorder treatment.
13 Sec. 4. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
14 appropriations and allocations are made.
15 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
16 IV-E Foster Care/Adoption Assistance 0137
17 Initiative: Provides one-time funding for a 2-year pilot program to award contracts to 2
18 child abuse and neglect prevention councils in this State for a community navigator position
19 within each council.
